# Python / Flask Standards

## Route Handlers
- Use `request.form.get()` for POST data (never raw `request.form[]`)
- Validate all inputs before DB operations
- Always close cursors after use with `cur.close()`
- Commit transactions with `mysql.connection.commit()` after writes

## Error Handling
```python
# Always validate before DB writes
if not all([name, email, subject]):
    flash("Please fill in all fields.", "danger")
    return redirect(url_for("main.contact"))
```

## Security
- Never interpolate user input into SQL strings
- Always use parameterized queries: `cur.execute("SELECT * FROM users WHERE id = %s", (user_id,))`
- Hash passwords with `bcrypt.generate_password_hash()`
- Use `@login_required` on all authenticated routes
- Use `@admin_required` on all admin routes
